quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  40,21,"Have, they not journeyed on in the earth and seen how was the end of those who journeyed on before them? They were stronger than them in might, and their vestiges are in the land, but God caught them up in their sins, and they had none to guard them against God"
  40,22,"That is for that their apostles did come to them with manifest signs, and they misbelieved, and God caught them up; verily, He is mighty, keen to punish"
  40,23,"And we did send Moses with our signs, and with obvious authority"
  40,24,"unto Pharaoh and Haman and Qarun. They said, 'A lying sorcerer"
  40,25,"and when they came to them with truth from us, they said, 'Kill the sons of those who believe with him, and let their women live!' but the stratagem of the misbelievers is only in error"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, 'Let me kill Moses; and then let him call upon his Lord! verily, I fear that he will change your religion, or that he will cause evil doing to appear in the land"
  40,27,"And Moses said, 'Verily, I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every one who is big with pride and believes not on the day of reckoning"
  40,28,"And a believing man of Pharaoh's people, who concealed his faith, said, 'Will ye kill a man for saying, My Lord is God, when he has come to you with manifest signs from your Lord? and if he be a liar, against him is his lie; and if he be truthful, there will befall you somewhat of that which he threatens you; verily, God guides not him who is an extravagant liar"
  40,29,"O my people! yours is the kingdom today, ye are eminent in the land, but who will help us against the violence of God, if it comes upon us?' Said Pharaoh, 'I will only show you what I see, and I will only guide you into the way of right direction"
  40,30,"And he who believed said, 'O my people! verily, I fear for you the like of the day of the confederates"
  40,31,"the like of the wont of the people of Noah and 'Ad and Haman, and of those after them; for God desires not injustice for His servants"
  40,32,"O my people! verily, I fear for you the day of crying out"
  40,33,"the day when ye shall turn your backs, fleeing, with no defender for you against God; for he whom God leads astray, for him there is no guide"
  40,34,"And Joseph came to you before with manifest signs, but ye ceased not to doubt concerning what he brought you, until, when he perished, ye said, \"God will not send after him an apostle;\" thus does God lead astray him who is extravagant, a doubter"
  40,35,Those who wrangle concerning the signs of God without authority having come to them are greatly hated by God and by those who believe; thus does God set a stamp upon the heart of every tyrant too big with pride
  40,36,"And Pharaoh said, 'O Haman! build for me a tower, haply I may reach the tracts"
  40,37,"the tracts of heaven, and may mount up to the God of Moses, for, verily, I think him a liar.' And thus was his evil deed made seemly to Pharaoh, and he was turned from the way; but Pharaoh's stratagem ended only in ruin"
  40,38,"and he who believed said, 'O my people! follow me, I will guide you to the way of the right direction"
  40,39,"O my people! verily, the life of this world is but a provision, but, verily, the hereafter, that is the abode of stability"
  40,40,"Whoso does evil, he shall only be recompensed with the like thereof , and whoso does right, be it male or female and a believer, these shall enter into Paradise; they shall be provided therein without count"